[2026-03-02 10:25:41] Engine: Checking Condition - Field: abstract | Operator: is_empty | Expected:  | Actual: The article analyzes Russian language, which forms the spiritual space of the Russian people. Its aim is to demonstrate that Russian language possesses a strong spiritual essence, the way we decode the theological knowledge Russian language contains through the language units. The integrative methods, driven by the multifaceted nature of such phenomena as language, religion, society, culture, and consciousness are used. General scientific methods (observation, description, generalization) and modern techniques of discourse and cognitive analysis are among them. As a result, we come to the conclusion that Russian language accumulates Russian people spirit, and Russian person is a "symphonic personality," according to L.P. Karsavin. However, God is the conductor, so Russian person understanding is impossible without taking religious values ​​into account. The research significance containes an attempt to overcome the limits of rational cognition and move into intuitive-theological perspective, that will be facilitated religious and scientific efforts and knowledge combining. The construction of a religious linguistic personality model based on religious communication is a long-term prospect of this spiritual person approach.
